# Netflix SQL Analysis Project

## Overview
This project is a SQL-based analysis of a Netflix-style dataset using MySQL Workbench. The goal is to analyze content distribution, ratings, countries, and release trends.

## Dataset
- Source: Generated Netflix dataset
- Total Records: 1000
- Columns: 12

## Objective
To perform data analysis using SQL and extract meaningful business insights from Netflix content data.

## Tools Used
- MySQL Workbench
- SQL
- GitHub

## SQL Concepts Used
- SELECT
- WHERE
- ORDER BY
- GROUP BY
- HAVING
- CASE WHEN
- JOINS
- Subqueries
- CTE
- Window Functions (ROW_NUMBER, RANK, DENSE_RANK, LAG, LEAD)
- Views
- Indexes

## Key Analysis Performed
- Movies vs TV Shows distribution
- Top countries with most content
- Most common ratings
- Release year trends
- Latest and oldest titles
- Ranking using window functions

## Files in Repository
- Netflix_SQL_Project.sql → All SQL queries
- netflix_titles_generated.csv → Dataset
- README.md → Project documentation

## Conclusion
This project demonstrates SQL skills used in real-world data analysis including filtering, aggregation, joins, and window functions.
